# JIRA MCP FALLBACK (REST READ) [CRITICAL]

42. [CRITICAL] **Jira issue reads:** Prefer **Jira MCP**. If Jira MCP is unavailable or fails after **2–3 retries** with backoff, agents MUST use the **Atlassian REST API v3** read fallback for **full** issue-equivalent data (same evidence expectations as MCP: `expand=names`, custom fields, links, attachments metadata; attachment body via **`Cursor-Project/config/jira/download-jira-attachments.ps1`** when needed). **Secrets:** only from env / MCP config — never in rules or chat (**Rule DB.1** pattern). Disclose in chat: **`Jira source: REST fallback …`**. **Canonical:** `.cursor/rules/integrations/jira_rest_fallback.mdc`. Abandoning Jira-backed work when REST could satisfy the read **without** user opt-out is a CRITICAL SYSTEM ERROR.

# CONFLUENCE MCP FALLBACK (REST READ) [CRITICAL]

43. [CRITICAL] **Confluence reads:** Prefer **Confluence MCP**. If Confluence MCP is unavailable or fails after **2–3 retries** with backoff, agents MUST use the **Confluence Cloud REST** read fallback for **read-equivalent** page/search data (same read-only posture as MCP; **no** Confluence writes). **Secrets / base URL:** only from env / MCP config — **`CONFLUENCE_WIKI_BASE`**, or derive from **`CONFLUENCE_URL`** / **`JIRA_BASE_URL`** (see **`confluence_rest_fallback.mdc`**), plus **`JIRA_EMAIL`/`JIRA_API_TOKEN`** or **`CONFLUENCE_EMAIL`/`CONFLUENCE_API_TOKEN`** — never in rules or chat (**Rule DB.1** pattern). Disclose in chat: **`Confluence source: REST fallback …`**. **Canonical:** `.cursor/rules/integrations/confluence_rest_fallback.mdc`; helper script: **`Cursor-Project/config/confluence/get-confluence-page-rest.ps1`**. Abandoning mandatory Confluence read steps when REST could satisfy the read **without** user opt-out is a CRITICAL SYSTEM ERROR.

# JIRA TICKET ANALYSIS + LINKED CONFLUENCE [CRITICAL]

44. [CRITICAL] When the user requests **Jira issue** analysis, triage, summary, or retrieval, and the issue contains **in-scope Confluence URLs**, agents MUST read those pages in the **same** pass as the ticket analysis (**`.cursor/rules/main/evidence_only_project_answers.mdc`** — *Jira ticket analysis — linked Confluence*). Use **Rule 39** scope (linked pages only unless the user asks or the user is running **Rule 32** / **`bug-validator`**) and **Rule 43** for MCP/REST. **Bug** issue type alone does **not** authorize broad Confluence search outside **`bug-validator`**. Skipping readable linked Confluence when the user asked for ticket analysis **without** user opt-out is a CRITICAL SYSTEM ERROR.
